   <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="title:1;14:26">Heat Sink Requirements</title>
   <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="body:1;17:24">
      <note audience="MSCCInternal" class="- topic/note " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="note:1;21:27">
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:1;24:24">Data sourced from PMC-2020246 Attaching Passive Heat Sinks to Organic Flip Chip Packages, Issue 4.00</p>
      </note>
      <section id="section_Package_Construction_3j4kcqljt" class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="section:1;29:33">
         <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="title:2;32:32">Package Construction</title>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:2;35:24">The 40x40 mm switch package uses an integrated heat spreader. The basic construction of the switch package is shown in <xref href="#xd_f8bcb077205a5927--42109557-15cf9f08a40--7ef3/fig_FCBGA_with_heat_spreader_1j4kcek05" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="xref:1;38:33" type="fig"><?ditaot gentext?>Figure 1</xref>. It can be seen that the lid or thermal spreader is a non-integral part of the package. A relatively small torque in the plane of the lid could cause the lid to break off. Care must be taken such that loads are applied evenly when attaching heat sinks and otherwise handling the devices.</p>
         <fig id="fig_FCBGA_with_heat_spreader_1j4kcek05" class="- topic/fig " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="fig:1;42:28">
            <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="title:3;45:35">FCBGA with heat spreader</title>
            <image href="graphics/trident_thermal_pkg_fcbga_w_hs.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="image:1;50:36"/>
         </fig>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:3;54:24">The 29x29 mm switch package has an exposed die. The basic construction of the switch package is shown in<xref href="#xd_f8bcb077205a5927--42109557-15cf9f08a40--7ef3/fig_FCBGA_with_no_heat_spreader_exposed-die__2j4kcek05" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="xref:2;57:33" type="fig"><?ditaot gentext?>Figure 2</xref> . This type of packaging option is beneficial for heat sinking applications as it greatly reduces the thermal resistance between the junction and the heat sink, but care must be taken when attaching the heat sink so as not to incur damage to the die itself.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:4;60:24">This type of packaging option is beneficial for heat sinking applications as it greatly reduces the thermal resistance between the junction and the heat sink, but care must be taken when attaching the heat sink so as not to incur damage to the die itself.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:5;63:25"/>
         <fig id="fig_FCBGA_with_no_heat_spreader_exposed-die__2j4kcek05" class="- topic/fig " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="fig:2;67:28">
            <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="title:4;70:35">FCBGA with no heat spreader (exposed-die)</title>
            <image href="graphics/trident_thermal_pkg_fcbga_wo_hs.png" width="258" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="image:2;76:36"/>
         </fig>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:6;80:24">In general, it is recommended that all heat sinks be clamped to the board directly so that mechanical pressure on the package is normal to the lid. However, if proper precautions are used a direct attach of the heat sink to the package may be used.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:7;83:24">Any torque or stressful contact is to be applied with the package temperature kept &lt;30C. Further torque or vibration at higher temperatures should be minimized.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:8;86:24">For vertically mounted components, customers should beware of shear forces on the package lid, induced by the weight of the heat sink, possibly leading to lid detachment as well, even if the torque is below the failure limit as discussed in <xref href="#xd_f8bcb077205a5927--42109557-15cf9f08a40--7ef3/section_Maximum_Allowable_Torque_1ifygfaek" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="xref:3;89:33" type="section"><?ditaot gentext?>Maximum Allowable Torque</xref>,</p>
      </section>
      <section id="section_PCB-mounted_Heat_Sinks_0ifyfkl3y" class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="section:2;94:33">
         <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="title:5;97:32">PCB-mounted Heat Sinks</title>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:9;100:24">Heat sinks mounted using mechanical fasteners to the printed circuit board provide the most robust attachment method and isolates the device and the package lid from adverse torque and shear forces. There are various methods to accomplishing this type of heat sink attachment, from removable standoffs and press-fit hardware, to solderable anchors and wire clips. The heat sink vendor chosen by the customer will have details on the methods offered. Again, care should be taken to apply the attachment force with uniform distribution. </p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:10;103:25">At normal operation, the maximum allowed compressive force on the packaged device can be calculated using the following formulae: </p>
         <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="codeblock:1;104:196">Maximum pressure tolerance = (number of balls) x (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="i:1;104:386">W</i> grams/solder ball)</codeblock>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:11;107:25">The values of <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="i:2;109:27">W</i> can be: </p>
         <ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="ul:1;112:26">
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="li:1;115:29">
               <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:12;118:31">For operating temperatures higher than 85C at the solder balls, use 4 grams/solder ball <ph audience="PMCInternal" class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="ph:1;121:35">(e.g. &lt;10 lbs. for 1152 BGA parts)</ph>. Use this value if not certain about the temperature.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="li:2;125:29">
               <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:13;128:31">For operating temperatures lower than 85C at the solder balls, use 8 grams/solder ball <ph audience="PMCInternal" class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="ph:2;131:35">(e.g. &lt;20 lbs. for 1152 BGA parts)</ph>. </p>
            </li>
         </ul>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:14;136:25">The pressure applied must not exceed the maximum allowed pressure in order to avoid damage to the device. </p>
         <note class="- topic/note " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="note:2;139:30">When attaching a heat sink to the package, the absolute maximum downward pressure to the package can be as high as 40 grams/ball, only if attachment is performed at room temperature. </note>
      </section>
      <section id="section_Package-clipped_Heat_Sinks_1ifyfkl3y" class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="section:3;144:33">
         <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="title:6;147:32">Package-clipped Heat Sinks</title>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:15;150:25">If the heat sink to be used has a base dimension less than or equal to the outer dimensions of the flip-chip package, the heat sink can be attached to the package directly using flexible polymer or metal clips. This type of attachment method secures the heat sink to the package by way of spring compression of a polymer or metal clip between the package substrate and the heat sink base. This arrangement can be seen in <xref href="#xd_f8bcb077205a5927--42109557-15cf9f08a40--7ef3/fig_Heat_Sink_Attachment_using_Package_Clip_4j4kcqljt" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="xref:4;153:33" type="fig"><?ditaot gentext?>Figure 3</xref>.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:16;156:25">This attachment method is acceptable only if the sustained compression force provided by the clip does not exceed the maximum allowable pressure detailed in <xref href="#section_PCB-mounted_Heat_Sinks_0ifyfkl3y" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="xref:5;159:33"><?ditaot gentext?>#section_PCB-mounted_Heat_Sinks_0ifyfkl3y</xref> and only if the device is mounted horizontally. </p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:17;162:25">For the 40x40 mm package, package-clipped heat sink attachment for vertically mounted packages shown in <xref href="#xd_f8bcb077205a5927--42109557-15cf9f08a40--7ef3/fig_Heat_Sink_Attachment_using_Package_Clip_4j4kcqljt" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="xref:6;165:34" type="fig"><?ditaot gentext?>Figure 3</xref> is to be avoided. PCB-mounted attachment is to be used in these situations.</p>
         <fig id="fig_Heat_Sink_Attachment_using_Package_Clip_4j4kcqljt" class="- topic/fig " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="fig:3;169:28">
            <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="title:7;172:35">Heat Sink Attachment using Package Clip</title>
            <image href="graphics/trident_thermal_pkg_mount_heatsink.png" width="5in" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="image:3;178:36"/>
         </fig>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:18;182:25">For exposed-die packages, 29x29 mm, it is potentially hazardous to the device to attach the heat sink directly to the die surface without additional pressure distribution. Because of the limited surface area of the die, the heat sink attachment can induce large stress concentrations on the package and the die itself. It is recommended that exposed-die packages employ a PCB-mounted solution, however if a package-clipped heat sink is desired, a spacer of semi-compliant material must be placed around the die perimeter to distribute attachment pressure evenly as shown in<xref href="#xd_f8bcb077205a5927--42109557-15cf9f08a40--7ef3/fig_Heat_Sink_Attachment_using_Package_Clip__5j4kcqljt" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="xref:7;185:33" type="fig"><?ditaot gentext?>Figure 4</xref> . The precise material and thickness of spacer for the required application should be discussed with the heat sink supplier.</p>
         <fig id="fig_Heat_Sink_Attachment_using_Package_Clip__5j4kcqljt" class="- topic/fig " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="fig:4;189:28">
            <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="title:8;192:35">Heat Sink Attachment using Package Clip for Exposed-die Package</title>
