      <section id="section_Epoxy_Heat_Sink_Attachment_0ifygfaek" class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="section:5;248:33">
         <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="title:11;251:33">Epoxy Heat Sink Attachment</title>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:23;254:25">In general, epoxy heat sink attachment is not recommended. </p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:24;257:25">If thermally conductive epoxy is to be used out of necessity, special attention should be paid to the following items:</p>
         <ol class="- topic/ol " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="ol:1;260:26">
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="li:3;263:29">
               <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:25;266:31">Adhesive thickness must be uniform and centered on the package top. An ‘X’ pattern is recommended for even distribution under application pressure, however heat sink geometries may require alternative patterns for best coverage. </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="li:4;270:29">
               <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:26;273:31">Heating/cooling rate must fall within the limits of what is allowed for normal reflow. The peak temperature should be kept as low as possible as the adhesive strength for the lid decreases significantly at higher temperatures (&gt;100oC). </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="li:5;277:29">
               <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:27;280:31">Heat sinks must be removed before any solder rework or when demounting a package from the PCB. The package coupled with an external heat sink would have a very large thermal mass that would require prolonged heating for any solder rework. This excessive heating may cause permanent degradation to the package lid and/or stiffener adhesive. </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="li:6;284:29">
               <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:28;287:31">Epoxy heat sink attachment for vertically mounted packages shown in <xref href="#xd_f8bcb077205a5927--42109557-15cf9f08a40--7ef3/fig_Worst-Case_Static_Shear_on_a_Vertically__3ifygfaek" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="xref:11;290:40" type="fig"><?ditaot gentext?>Figure 7</xref> is to be avoided. PCB-mounted attachment is to be used in these situations.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="li:7;294:29">
               <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\package\trident_package_heatsink_requirements.xml" xtrc="p:29;297:31">Care must be taken to avoid any excessive external forces, such as those caused through vibration, stress (e.g. mismatched coefficients of thermal expansion between the heat sink and the lid), and accidental strikes or other mechanical shocks, to the heat sinks attached with thermal epoxy.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </section>
